It’s an honour to be a part of the Ultrasuoni Rimini Festival on 10th June 2023 in memory of Mr. Thomas Balsamini. 

The 10th June 2023 will be ten years since Thomas Balsamini’s passing, he was the owner of the historical Velvet Club in Rimini. We have very fond memories of playing the Velvet Club several times. Thomas was a local celebrity in Rimini who invested money and his entire life in the music promotion. We are incredible humbled to be invited to be part of what will be a magical charity event to honour Mr. Thomas Balsamini’s memory. 

🔗 Tickets are available to purchase via our link in bio

URGENT APPEAL: Forty years ago, Simon Cowell (Not X Factor) founded the Wildlife Aid Foundation, which has saved hundreds of thousands of animals' lives. It comes with great sadness to say that Simon has been diagnosed with terminal cancer. Since the diagnosis, the charity faces a devastating crisis. We need YOUR help to fund the charity's relocation to new land. Time is running out. We made a video with Chesney Hawkes' hit 'The One and Only' to raise funds. Together we can make a difference. Let's get it to #1 and help save the wildlife! 

📺 Watch it via our link in bio.

This uplifting, soulful and soaring rendition is part fundraiser part tribute.

A note from Skin - 

“Brixton is an incredible venue that has had Gentrification vultures circling over it for decades and now because of recent events the Police are in league with them to destroy one of the country’s most legendary venues. We need to band together to stop this! Brixton is the cultural centre of South London, music is its heart! We do not need more expensive exclusive apartments run by greedy Landlords that have ruined so much of our city, we need venues like Brixton to be run efficiently and properly with honest workers of which Brixton has many! So please sign this petition to stop the closure of Brixton Academy. As a Brixtioner and band member who has performed many times there, the end of Brixton Academy who be a devastating loss for Brixton and music! Please share and sign, I urge everyone in a band who has played there or who has been to see a gig there to sign and share!”

🔗 SIGN THE PETITION via our link in bio. 

🙏 SAVE BRIXTON ACADEMY head over to @ntiaofficial 

Please share these links across socials as well as with your friends and family. Let’s work together to save Brixton Academy! 

#SaveBrixtonAcademy #SaveBrixton #BrixtonAcademy

Listen to Mark on share his story of recovery and hope on @thenodpod and the role motorbikes has played in that story with @charleyboorman @iambenbowers and @iammrpartridge 

On the @thenodpod - Of his recovery in general Mark says… ‘Far from being self-indulgent, my hope is that others might reach out to share their fears, worries and feelings rather than keeping things submerged under a mask of ‘I’m fine’. There are too many suicides in general, especially in men aged 45-55, so it’s important to share. But whatever age, race or gender check in on that mate you haven’t seen for a while. Ask them how they are …then ask them again. Learn to listen without judgment or advice giving. Reply with ’I hear you’ or ‘that sounds tough is there anything I can do?’ That’s enough'
